'''Mehdi Torabi'''{{Efn|{{langx|fa|مهدی ترابی}}}} (born 10 September 1994) is an Iranian professional [[Football player|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (football)|winger]] for [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] club [[Tractor S.C.|Tractor]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].

He began his career at [[Saipa F.C.|Saipa]], and then played for [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] between 2019 and 2020. He played for Qatari side [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi]] between 2020 and 2021, later rejoining Persepolis. He joined Tractor in 2024 and has been regarded as the club's fan favorite.

Torabi made his first senior appearance in 2015, and represented Iran at the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]], and the [[AFC Asian Cup]] in [[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019]] and [[2023 AFC Asian Cup|2023]].

== Early life and family ==
Mahdi Torabi was born on 10 September 1994 in [[Karaj]], [[Alborz province]], Iran.

==Club career==
===Saipa===
Torabi's career began with the [[Saipa F.C.|Saipa]] youth squad. He was promoted to the first team by [[Mojtaba Taghavi]] in the summer of 2012. He made his debut in the [[2013–14 Persian Gulf Cup]] season against [[Mes Kerman]] as a substitute for [[Kaveh Rezaei]].

[[File:Torabi And Mensha.jpg|thumb|Torabi playing for [[Saipa F.C.|Saipa]] against [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in 2018]]

===Persepolis===
[[File:Persepolis F.C. v Esteghlal F.C., 6 February 2020 (39).jpg|thumb|Torabi with [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in 2020]]
On 1 July 2018, Torabi signed a three-year deal with [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]]. He was sent on back on loan to Saipa for the first half of the season until Persepolis had served their transfer ban. On 16 December 2018, Torabi officially joined Persepolis' squad and was assigned the number 9.<ref>[https://90tv.ir/news/%DA%86%DA%A9-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%88%DB%8C%D9%87-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%B3%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%BE%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%AE-%D9%82%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%DB%8C-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%88%DB%8C%D9%84-%D8%B4%D8%AF چک-تسویه-حساب-با-سایپا-برای-فسخ-قرارداد-ترابی-تحویل-شد] {{Dead link|date=August 2022}}</ref>

Torabi scored his first goal for Persepolis in a 3–2 victory over Saipa on 13 April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yjc.ir/fa/news/6896873/|title=اولین گل ستاره پرسپولیس به تیم سابقش|website=www.yjc.ir|date=13 April 2019 |language=fa|access-date=24 May 2019}}</ref>

=== Al-Arabi ===
In October 2020, Torabi joined [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi]] and played in the [[Qatar Stars League]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-10-09 |title=Mahdi Torabi handed Al Arabi No.99 |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/453353/Mehdi-Torabi-handed-Al-Arabi-No-99 |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=Tehran Times |language=en}}</ref>

=== Return to Persepolis ===
In February 2021, he rejoined Persepolis to play in the Persian Gulf Pro League.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Fan favourite Mahdi Torabi back with Persepolis |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/more/news/fan_favourite_mehdi_torabi_back_with_persepolis.html |access-date=2025-11-23 |website=the-AFC |language=en}}</ref>

=== Tractor ===
In the summer of 2024, it was announced that he wanted to transfer to another team for more income but he himself said that he changed his team to improve his mental condition, not to earn money.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-10 |title=مهدی ترابی به تراکتور پیوست؛ "پول نه، از نظر روحی و فنی نیاز داشتم تغییر تیم بدهم" |url=https://www.iranintl.com/202407100234 |access-date=2024-07-10 |website=ایران اینترنشنال |language=fa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-23 |title=معمای مهدی ترابی؛ رد پیشنهاد ۴۵ میلیاردی پرسپولیس و دریافت ۵۰۰ هزار دلار از تراکتور؟ |url=https://www.mashreghnews.ir/news/1616618/%D9%85%D8%B9%D9%85%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%87%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%AF-%DB%B4%DB%B5-%D9%85%DB%8C%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D9%88-%D8%AF%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AA-%DB%B5%DB%B0%DB%B0 |access-date=2024-07-10 |website=مشرق نیوز |language=fa}}</ref>

On 10 July 2024, Torabi joined [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] side [[Tractor S.C.|Tractor]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Mahdi Torabi Joins Tractor: IPL - Sports news - Tasnim News Agency |url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2024/07/10/3120336/mehdi-torabi-joins-tractor-ipl |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20251010065715/https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2024/07/10/3120336/mehdi-torabi-joins-tractor-ipl |archive-date=2025-10-10 |access-date=2025-11-23 |work=Tasnim News Agency |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth level===
He was invited to [[Iran national under-23 football team|Iran U23]] preliminary camp by [[Nelo Vingada]].<ref name="tabnak">{{cite web|url=http://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/380334/89-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C%DA%A9%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF%D9%88%DB%8C-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D9%81%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%BE%DB%8C%DA%A9|title=89 بازیکن در اردوی تیم فوتبال المپیک - سایت خبری تحلیلی تابناك|date=19 February 2014 |publisher=tabnak.ir|accessdate=12 August 2014}}</ref> Torabi was included in the squad for the [[2016 AFC U-23 Championship]] by coach [[Mohammad Khakpour]] and he scored his first goal of the tournament in the last group match against China from a 30-yard free kick.

===Senior level===
[[File:IRN-VIETNAM 20190112 Asian Cup 28.jpg|thumb|Torabi in the match between [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]] and [[Iran national football team|Iran]] at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]]]]

He made his debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a friendly on 11 June 2015 where he scored the lone goal of the match. On 3 September 2015, Torabi came off the bench to score in a 6–0 victory against [[Guam national football team|Guam]]. In May 2018 he was named in Iran's [[Iran national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/440833652018|title=World Cup 2018: All the confirmed squads for this summer's finals in Russia}}{{dead link|date=September 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> In November 2022, Torabi was listed in Iran's squad for the 2022 FIFA World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |author1=Greg Lea Contributions from Michael Yokhin |date=2022-11-25 |title=Iran World Cup 2022 squad: Carlos Queiroz announces final 25-man team |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/iran-world-cup-2022-squad-dragan-skocic-names-his-latest-squad |access-date=2025-11-22 |website=FourFourTwo |language=en}}</ref>

==Personal life==
===Political views===
Torabi is a supporter of the [[government of the Islamic Republic of Iran]], having worn a shirt in support of Supreme Leader [[Ali Khamenei]] and wanting to offer him a football as a gift during the [[Mahsa Amini protests]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 November 2022 |title=Iran Has More Than Just Soccer On Its Mind At The World Cup |url=https://defector.com/iran-has-more-than-just-soccer-on-its-mind-at-the-world-cup/ |website=defector.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=28 October 2022 |title=Solidarity with Iran revolution prominent across soccer world |url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/solidarity-with-iran-revolution-prominent-across-soccer-world-20221025-WST-405779.html |website=World Soccer Talk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ele vai: conheça Torabi, atacante habilidoso e adulador de líder supremo do Irã |url=https://br.noticias.yahoo.com/ele-vai-conhe%C3%A7a-torabi-atacante-080109455.html |website=br.noticias.yahoo.com}}</ref> In 2019, Torabi lifted his shirt up with a message of support to the government during the [[2019–2020 Iranian protests]] as well. The literal translation of his message was "The only path to salvation of country is to follow orders of the leader".<ref name="iranwire">{{Cite web |title=Footballers Tackle the Regime |url=https://iranwire.com/en/sports/108280-footballers-tackle-regime/ |website=iranwire.com}}</ref>

